    "These results underline the method's strength in leveraging detailed explanations to enhance model understanding and performance significantly.",
    "In this section, we conduct an ablation study to investigate the importance of each component in the ELAD framework we propose, and the results are reported in Table 2.",
    "The results reveal that the full proposed ELAD framework outperforms configurations lacking EGSS (w/o EGSS) and CLAER (w/o CLAER) across all tasks.",
    "Ours demonstrates a notable performance advantage, with improvements up to 2.41% in arithmetic tasks, 6.88% in NLI tasks, and 5.09% in commonsense reasoning tasks over the \"w/o EGSS\" setup.",
    "This highlights the critical contributions of EGSS and CLAER to the framework's overall performance."
